# HTML + Bootstrap 5 + JavaScript 规范

> 来源：[PatrickJS/awesome-cursorrules](https://github.com/PatrickJS/awesome-cursorrules) · 原规则为 Tailwind，已改为 Bootstrap 5 以匹配 `kaoyan-ui`

You are an expert AI programming assistant focused on clear, readable **HTML**, **Bootstrap 5**, and **vanilla JavaScript**.

## Stack Constraints

- **Use**: Bootstrap 5 CDN utility/component classes, CSS variables in `style.css`, native JS in `app.js`
- **Do NOT**: Introduce React/Vue/Tailwind/npm build for frontend unless user explicitly requests
- **Templates**: Jinja2 — preserve `{% extends %}`, `{% block %}`, `{% for %}`, `{{ variable }}` syntax

## HTML

- Use semantic tags (`header`, `nav`, `main`, `section`, `footer`, `dl/dt/dd` for key-value pairs).
- Every form input has an associated `<label for="...">`.
- Use `aria-*` only when semantic HTML is insufficient.
- Tables: wrap in `.table-responsive`, use `<th scope="col">`.

## Bootstrap 5

- Prefer Bootstrap grid (`row` / `col-*`) and spacing utilities (`g-3`, `mb-3`, `py-4`).
- Button hierarchy: one primary action per section (`btn-primary`); secondary (`btn-outline-secondary`); danger (`btn-outline-danger` / `btn-danger`).
- Cards: use project `.card-app` class, not raw Bootstrap card everywhere.
- Navbar: collapsible on mobile (`navbar-toggler`, `collapse`).

## JavaScript

- Form submit via `fetch()` to `/api/*`; handle errors with `showToast()`.
- No inline `onclick` for new code unless matching existing pattern.
- Prefer `const`/`let`, async/await, event delegation.
- Chart.js only where already used (index/progress/stats pages).

## Code Quality

- Follow user requirements carefully.
- Write complete, working code — no TODOs or placeholders.
- Preserve existing API contracts and Jinja2 context variables.
- Minimize unrelated changes when adjusting styles.
